8.02	Yashwant_Sinha	Yashwant Sinha	Yashwant Sinha (born November 6, 1937, Patna) is an Indian politician and a former finance minister of India (1990–1991 under Prime Minister Chandra Shekhar and March 1998 – July 2002 under Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee) and foreign minister (July 2002 – May 2004) in Atal Bihari Vajpayee's cabinet. He is a senior leader of the Bharatiya Janata Party, currently the largest Opposition party in India.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d7/Yashwant_Sinha_IMF.jpg/220px-Yashwant_Sinha_IMF.jpg
